value.value: Adult T-cell leukemia/lymphoma affecting the skin.
The act of distributing or spreading or apportioning.
Indicates the person or authoritative body who has distributed something.
The act or process of following a person, animal, or object through space or time.

The highest taxonomic rank, immediately above phylum or division. There are five biological kingdoms (Monera, Protista, Plantae, Fungi, Animalia) into which organisms are grouped, based on common characteristics.
A major division of a biological kingdom, consisting of closely-related classes; represents a basic fundamental pattern of organization and, presumably, a common descent.
A taxonomic group ranking between a phylum and a class.
A written record of events.
A rare benign neoplasm that arises from the renal pelvis and is characterized by the presence of a papillary growth with a central fibrovascular core. The latter is lined by normal urothelium.

A collection of taxonomic subdivisions directly under Phylum. It is a major group of organisms, e.g. Mammalia, Reptilia, Gastropoda, Insecta, etc that contains a large number of different sublineages, but have shared characteristics in common (e.g. warm-blooded, fur, six legs etc).
Something perceptible by one or more of the senses, especially by vision or touch; a material thing.
The single one of its kind.
A person responsible for organizing multiple events or efforts into a smaller number of tasks.
A taxonomic subdivisions more specific than class but more general than order.
A taxonomic category of related organisms ranking below a subclass and above an order.
A taxonomic category between Class and Family.  It is group of organisms that although differing quite a bit among themselves still have a large degree of characteristics in common.
A taxonomic group that is a subdivision of an order.
A taxonomic category of related organisms ranking below a suborder and above a family.
Stage 0is includes: Tis, N0, M0.  Tis: Carcinoma in situ.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 7th ed.)
A taxonomic category between Order and Genus. It consists of a group of organisms among which the differences are quite minor, e.g. Equiidae - horses and their relatives.
A taxonomic category below a family.
A taxonomic category ranking below a family (or Subfamily) and above a species and generally consisting of a group of species exhibiting similar characteristics.
A group of organisms that differ from all other groups of organisms and that are capable of breeding and producing fertile offspring.
A dimension table that lists the specimen requirements for this protocol. Specimen requirements include: SPECIMEN_TYPE, SPECIMEN_QUANT, and DISEASE_STATUS. (caTISSUE)
An indication that expression of CD4 has been detected in a sample of neoplastic cells.
An immunophenotypic finding indicating the presence of neoplastic cells expressing CD56.
Jelly like material formed by the coagulation of a colloidal liquid.
A substance in the fluid state of matter having no fixed shape but a fixed volume.
A fluid in the gaseous state having neither independent shape nor volume and being able to expand indefinitely.
Biologically active DNA which has been formed by the in vitro joining of segments of DNA from different sources usually for the purpose of genetic manipulation.
An exophytic and polypoid lesion attached to the ureter by a broad base or a thin stalk.
The state in which a substance has no tendency to flow under moderate stress; resists forces (such as compression) that tend to deform it; and retains a definite size and shape.
A brittle transparent solid with irregular atomic structure.
A solid substance in the form of tiny loose particles; a solid that has been pulverized.
A suspension of fine drops of a liquid in a gas.
A mixture in which fine particles are suspended in a fluid where they are supported by buoyancy.
A substance consisting of two or more substances mixed together (not in fixed proportions and not with chemical bonding).
Any matter of defined composition that has discrete existence, whose origin may be biological, mineral or chemical.
A gel matrix through which molecules are separated, usually by size or charge, under the influence of an electrical field.
An electrophoresis gel composed of agarose dissolved in an aqueous buffer.
An electrophoresis gel composed of polyacrylamide in an aqueous buffer.

Stage 0is includes: (Tis, N0, M0); (Tis pu, N0, M0); (Tis pd, N0, M0).  Tis: Carcinoma in situ.  Tis pu: Carcinoma in situ, involvement of the prostatic urethra.  Tis pd: Carcinoma in situ, involvement of the prostatic ducts.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 7th ed.)
